Descriptions. Mature larva (final instar) (
Fig. 5
)—Length: body 4.5–4.9 mm ; cercus and median caudal filament subequal, each 2.2–2.6 mm . General color light brown with variable brown shading and markings; body and legs covered with long, hairlike setae.

Abdomen: Basal coloration pale to light brown. Anterior abdominal terga with dark lateral patches and median longitudinal streak (
Fig. 6
); posterior terga basal coloration pale; tergum 9 with dark purple shading. Abdominal sterna pale with purple-brown lateral maculae. Genitalia (as in
Fig. 2
) pale to light brown. Penes lobes apically rounded. Forceps segment 2 with slight distal expansion; forceps segment 3 subovoid. Cercus and median caudal filament white with long hairlike setae abundant.

